name: Nice,new app. nearby Center/Jordaan
host_about:
I’m 38 years old and I live in Amsterdam for more than 10 years now. My boyfriend (Thomas) and I bought this totally renovated apartment 10 years ago. We love our house because of its central location and the nice view over the water of the Da Costakade. It feels like a private lake just in front of our door. When the sun comes out our garden-side balcony is the perfect place for a morning breakfast and coffee. And in the afternoon we often enjoy a glass of wine on our French balcony on the other side of the apartment, watching many boats come by on the canal. 
Last summer we discovered the Amsterdam canals with our own private boat. Being near the water or on the water is one of the most relaxing things you can do in this city (there’s a boat rental nearby if you would like to try).  We also enjoy cooking and dining at home or somewhere else in the city. If you are interested I can give you some nice tips for sightseeing, shopping, the best coffee place, bakery and dining places in the neighbourhood.
I hope you like it as much as we do!

neighborhood_overview:
AMSTERDAM CENTRUM - CITY CENTER + CANAL DISTRICT
In addition to the world-famous historic Canal Ring, Amsterdam's City Centre district ('Centrum') is home to a host of renowned museums, charming and high-end shopping areas, fantastic culture and entertainment.
Amsterdam’s renowned art and culture and top shopping
In Amsterdam’s centre you will, of course, find the magnificent Canal Ring, but there is so much more besides. The inner city, for instance, is bursting with interesting museums, sometimes hidden behind beautiful canal-side façades. The diversity of the city centre’s culture is vast, from the emotional Anne Frank House in the west of the centre, through to the upbeat nature of Science Center NEMO in the east. In between, find an inspiring collection of art and history.
Top shopping
There is a vast array of shopping opportunities, from fashion brands and chains (Nieuwendijk, Kalverstraat) through to independent innovators and inspiring market stalls,

name: Amsterdam, Tiny House with incredibe view
description:
Newly build (2018), wooden but luxurious tiny house. Private area. A lot of space around your tiny house and a huge field of grass (protected area for birds) in front of your glass doors.

How does it feel?

neighborhood_overview:
Most of the visitors (and I absolutely agree) love Durgerdam because you stay in a pristine authentic quiet place, where you can enjoy nature. But just a stone's throw away you will be in the city center of Amsterdam. On your bike or with 15 minutes by car, Uber or a taxi.

Re-opening in 2022. The closest supermarket, that also provides fresh fish, meat, flowers and good vegetarian food is 7 minutes away by bike. In the tiny house there is a book with suggestion
host_about:
How it all started...

In my humble opinion I am very privileged to live in one of the most special places in the world: Durgerdam (Amsterdam - North).  On a historical dyke (former fisherman village), next to the IJsselmeer lake, in the typical Dutch rural landscape, but still very close to the unique city of Amsterdam.

As television producer I did (and do)  travel  a lot and I am always a fan of remarkable, unique accommodations to sleep and to stay in. Especially  excited do I get  when they are placed in the middle of nature or at unique locations.  Inspired by my visits to those spots, I decided to build my own little house, with all the comfort you need on a special place; my hometown Durgerdam/Amsterdam North.

Together with an architect we created the Tiny House. An authentic small wouden house, where I hope a lot of other people feel at home and can enjoy the green area & of course Amsterdam..

name: Amazing apartment | nearby the Vondelpark & Centre
description: Enjoy this lovely and authentic apartment in Amsterdam. You will have a 2-floor apartment with 2 bedrooms and a modern bathroom with floor heating. It is located in a very quiet street in Amsterdam Oud-West, right around the corner of the great Vondelpark, Leidse Square, many shops, nice cafe's, restaurants and public transport. It is very easy accessible from both the city centre as Schiphol Airport. When you are looking for 2 bedrooms this apartment will be exactly it!
neighborhood_overview: Oud West is close to the city-centre and close to both Vondelpark and Rembrandtpark. Ten Katestraat market is an excellent outdoor market with its charming cross-street ‘Bellamystraat’ giving the area an old-fashion village vibe – complete with dance studio and blacksmith. Kinkerstraat is a multicultural area with a large shopping street filled with bars, restaurants, clothes etc. It’s criss-crossed with commercial streets, including Overtoom which has become a major interiors boulevard. Two of the city’s more interesting alternative cultural complexes, OT301 and Lab111, which both mix music, film and art, are located here. But for a real taste for the relaxed diversity of this neighbourhood, visit the sprawling terrace of Du Cap to truly witness all walks of life. And again: the whole city is pretty much nearby.

description:

Right off Sarphatipark in the "de Pijp" area of Amsterdam, we offer a peaceful, central oasis. Our home is bright, warm, and is the perfect base from which to explore the city. Great for travelers or those needing a soft landing when relocating to NL

neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam's de Pijp neighborhood, located just outside the canal-filled historical center, but boasts a young, bohemian vibe that is one of a kind. Full of shops, good restaurants and bars, and the adorable Sarphatipark, the neighborhood is lively and artistic, and a reprieve from the bustle of central Amsterdam. Cultural and historical sites are within walking distance, or easily reachable with the trams that run near the house.

We are near the Albert Cuyp market, the Amstel river, Sarphati Park, Museumkwartier, the Heineken Museum, RAI, and many other sites in Amsterdam, Vondelpark, Amstel train station, the University of Amsterdam, and many other key locations.
host_about:
As hosts: We are an artistic international couple who occasionally rent out our home when we are away. We take pride in providing a safe space for all, where guests feel welcome, comfortable, and at home. 

As guests: Avid travelers and curious explorers with a passion for seeing the world!

name: limehome Amsterdam Leidsekruisstraat | Queen Room
description: At limehome, we believe that everyone deserves a better place while traveling. A place to look forward to return to. A place designed to stay®. Whether you are looking for a home away from home or a quiet place to work - our apartments feature high-quality fittings including a premium hotel bed for restful nights & suite dreams. Our digital-enabled guest journey without a physical reception and staff on-site makes your stay more convenient.
neighborhood_overview: Our limehome is located in the middle of the lively Leidseplein neighbourhood. From here, you can easily reach all the main sights of the floating city on foot. In addition to the cultural attractions, you will also find popular bars, restaurants and theatres where street artists and local talent delight their audiences. Right on your doorstep is the Amsterdam canal belt, a system of canals that is considered exemplary architecture of the Golden Age and has earned Amsterdam the nickname Venice of the North. Thanks to its proximity to the Museum Quarter, you can also reach impressive city highlights such as the Rijksmuseum or the entrance to the Vondelpark in just a few minutes. The Leidseplein and Prinsengracht tram stops are less than a 5-minute walk away, where a dedicated bus line will even take you directly to Schiphol Airport. All in all, you are in perfect hands here to explore the most diverse facets of the Dutch capital.

name: Appartement in bruisend Amsterdam West
description: Enjoy our cozy apartment and discover bustling Amsterdam from the nicest neighborhood! You sit here perfectly between the cozy Jordaan, with its cozy cafes, markets and canals, and the green Westerpark, where you can walk, have a drink or a festival. Everything within easy reach for the ultimate Amsterdam experience!
neighborhood_overview: The Staatsliedenbuurt is a nice and cheerful neighborhood, located between the bustling Jordaan and the wonderful Westerpark. In and around the Staatsliedenbuurt there are plenty of beautiful restaurants and cozy bars. For example, the famous Café Restaurant Amsterdam (recognizable by our crockery) is just around the corner, just like Café Beurre. In addition, the supermarket (Albert Heijn and the Dirk Van Den Broek), the bakery (bakery Westerpark and Louf), cozy cafes (café De Pianist) and good Italian (Bella Storia) are steps away from the apartment. All in all, all the ingredients for a lovely stay in the Staatsliedenbuurt.
